      "span_text": "Granting the general assumptions of theories that attempt to account for the evolution of cooperation (e.g., that interactions between individuals in the population have a sufficiently large probability of continuing; [CITATION_1] and mindful of the caveats noted earlier, the present results suggest that cooperation does not evolve under circumstances such as those in the present study.",
